events.name: Next ’19 Extended Edmonton
events.description:
Next '19 Extended brings together developer communities around the world to take part in the Next ’19 experience.

These events are extensions of Next, and allow local developers to access exciting Next ’19 content, and engage with peers across the community through codelabs and speaker events.

Join us to be a part of this amazing first ever event in Edmonton. Meet people and get to know more about the GDG Cloud Edmonton chapter.

Registration is free; Limited seats. Come join us, enjoy some snacks and grab some fun swag.

Event sponsor: TEC Edmonton

events.name: Cloud Computing and Machine Learning for Data Science
events.description:
Please join us in our second gathering of the GDG Cloud Edmonton, where three of our presenters will be sharing their expertise in data science, cloud and machine learning:

(1) Ji Yang, Ph.D. in Computer engineering, University of Alberta,
Practical Tricks for Data Science Competition
(2) Jared Rewerts, Software Engineer at City of Edmonton
Elastic Cloud on Kubernetes
(3) Lingbo Tang, Software Developer at Intuit,
History of containerization

Join us to be a part of this amazing event in Edmonton. Meet people and get to know more about the GDG Cloud Edmonton chapter.

Registration is free; Limited seats. After the presentations, come join us to Craft Beer Market for drinks!

Event sponsor: TEC Edmonton, AlbertaAI

events.name: Business & Developers Meetup
events.description:
Google Developers Group Edmonton is collaborating with Startup TNT to bring you this special meetup for developers, entrepreneurs, founders, investors and mentors.

Please join us to discuss the latest topics in data science, Cloud, AI and machine learning, to learn about their latest tools and techniques and discover how to work with developers to drive value for your business.

Two of our presenters will be sharing their expertise in in data science, Cloud, AI and machine learning for driving business:

(1) Dr. Lihang Ying, Entrepreneur & President of AlbertaAI
Topic: AI Introduction and Required Human Intelligence in Applications: A Defect Detection Case Study

(2) Rui pan, Blockchain Solution Developer at ReWatt Power
Topic: Leveraging DLT and ML to simplify complexity in carbon offset trading

Time: 6-9pm on Oct. 17, 2019

Location: 2nd floor at PolarParkBrewing

Event co-organizer: TusStar, AlbertaAI

More about Start-Up TNT:
Start-Up TNT is a weekly happy hour meet-up for entrepreneurs, scientists and investors to make friends, have fun, and build an entrepreneur-led community in Edmonton.

events.name: Google Machine Learning Cloud Study Jam

venue.name: University of Alberta, Computing Science Centre, 2nd floor Atrium
venue.address_1: 2-59C Computing Science Centre, University of Alberta

events.description:
Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Google Cloud Machine Learning technologies as a team.

After the Study Jam, you’ll receive 30-days free access to the entire Qwiklabs catalogue, so you can keep developing your skills at home.

Complete all of the labs in the session’s quest, and you’ll earn an additional free month of access to Qwiklabs as well as a badge for your online profile.

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

The location is on the UA North campus, Computing Science Centre (CSC), classroom B-2

Registration is free; Limited seats. Come join us, enjoy some snacks and grab some fun swag.

upcoming.name: ##ONLINE## Firebase Study Jam - Learn to Build Web Apps
upcoming.description:
Want to get started building web apps? Learn how to do that with Firebase from our experienced developers!!!

The GDG Cloud Edmonton is hosting an ONLINE Firebase Study Jam which is best suited for:
1) those just getting started with developing web apps for desktop and mobile
2) those with programming experience on other mobile app frameworks

Together we'll work through Firebase for web codelabs prepared by Google instructors, and you will get hands-on experience with Firebase. This is a great opportunity to learn Firebase for developing Web applications from dedicated experts, share your experiences and network with other like-minded developers.

For the best experience, please check out Get Started with Firebase for Web (https://firebase.google.com/docs/web/setup).

This study event will be held ONLINE considering the outbreak of COVID-19, and more details will be provided soon.

Registration is free. Come join us and let's learn together.
